, 			{
				"box" : 				{
					"id" : "obj-2",
					"linecount" : 19,
					"maxclass" : "comment",
					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 1257.0, 24.0, 511.0, 261.0 ],
					"text" : "Scale and transform a 2d space including gamepad-specific features like a defineable deadzone and click-to-zoom.\n\nThis is intended to be used with dk.gridmatch but it can be used to process the output of dk.boppad, a gamepad, or any 2d controller.\n\nCan be controlled with the 2nd outlet of the node object or with the following attributes manually:\n@xyin = 4 item list consisting of {x low, x high, y low, y high} input scaling\n@xyout = 4 item list consisting of {x low, x high, y low, y high} output scaling\n@deadzone = defines deadzone amount\n@edgecase = defines what happens when input exceeds scaling (ignore or clip)\n@zoom = engage temporary zooming in\n@zoomamount = defines zoom amount (in %)\n@zoomfadein = time to crossfade over to zoomed scaling (in ms)\n@zoomfadeout = defines return speed out of zoom control (in ms)\n@curve = curve that is applied symmetrically each axis (-100 to 100)\n@transformation = transforms input space by turning a circlular input (gamepad) into a square (circ2square) or by turning a square input (trackpad) into a circle (square2circ)"
				}

			}
